  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit3_Distal_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit3_Distal_L
  partName: Forepaw Digit3 Distal Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left forepaw digit three distal phalanx forms the terminal portion of the
    third digit within the canine forepaw and supports the claw structure. This bone
    plays an important role in traction, grip, and coordinated toe movement during
    locomotion and interaction with surfaces.
  - Tendons attached to the distal phalanx control digital flexion and extension
    while maintaining balanced paw mechanics. The bone also protects soft tissues
    associated with the claw and contributes to efficient force distribution during
    movement.
